---
import StyleguideLayout from '../../layouts/StyleguideLayout.astro';
import Container from '../../components/Container.astro';
---

<StyleguideLayout title="Typography">
  <h1>Typography</h1>
    
  <p>
    A comprehensive showcase of all typography-related HTML elements organized by category.
  </p>

  <!-- Structural Elements -->
  <section>
    <h2>Structural Elements</h2>
    <p>Block-level elements that shape content flow and hierarchy.</p>
    
    <h3>Headings &lt;h1-6&gt;</h3>
    <Container>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h1>Heading 1</h1>
        <h2>Heading 2</h2>
        <h3>Heading 3</h3>
        <h4>Heading 4</h4>
        <h5>Heading 5</h5>
        <h6>Heading 6</h6>
      </div>
    </Container>

    <h3>Paragraph &lt;p&gt;</h3>
    <Container>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This is a paragraph element. It represents a block of text and is one of the most commonly used HTML elements. 
        Paragraphs automatically add spacing before and after themselves to improve readability.
      </p>
      <p>
        Multiple paragraphs are visually separated to create clear content boundaries and improve the reading experience.
      </p>
    </Container>

    <h3>Lists &lt;ul&gt;, &lt;ol&gt;, &lt;li&gt;</h3>
    <Container>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">Unordered List</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
            <li>First item</li>
            <li>Second item</li>
            <li>Third item
              <ul class="list-circle list-inside ml-6 mt-1">
                <li>Nested item</li>
                <li>Another nested item</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">Ordered List</h4>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1">
            <li>First step</li>
            <li>Second step</li>
            <li>Third step
              <ol class="list-decimal list-inside ml-6 mt-1">
                <li>Sub-step A</li>
                <li>Sub-step B</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>

    <h3>Definition List &lt;dl&gt;, &lt;dt&gt;, &lt;dd&gt;</h3>
    <Container>
      <dl class="space-y-3">
        <dt class="font-semibold">HTML</dt>
        <dd class="ml-6 text-secondary">HyperText Markup Language - the standard markup language for web pages.</dd>
        
        <dt class="font-semibold">CSS</dt>
        <dd class="ml-6 text-secondary">Cascading Style Sheets - used to describe the presentation of HTML documents.</dd>
        
        <dt class="font-semibold">JavaScript</dt>
        <dd class="ml-6 text-secondary">A programming language that enables interactive web pages and dynamic content.</dd>
      </dl>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- Inline Elements -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2>Inline Elements</h2>
    <p class="mb-8 text-secondary">Elements for emphasis and formatting within text.</p>
    
    <h3>Emphasis &amp; Importance</h3>
    <Container>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <p><em>&lt;em&gt;</em> - Emphasized text (semantic emphasis, typically italic)</p>
        <p><strong>&lt;strong&gt;</strong> - Strong importance (semantic strong, typically bold)</p>
        <p><i>&lt;i&gt;</i> - Idiomatic text (alternative voice or mood, typically italic)</p>
        <p><b>&lt;b&gt;</b> - Bold text (stylistic offset, no semantic importance)</p>
      </div>
    </Container>

    <h3>Text Modifications</h3>
    <Container>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <p><small>&lt;small&gt;</small> - Smaller text (fine print, side comments)</p>
        <p>E = mc<sup>2</sup> - &lt;sup&gt; Superscript text</p>
        <p>H<sub>2</sub>O - &lt;sub&gt; Subscript text</p>
        <p><ins>&lt;ins&gt;</ins> - Inserted text (underlined by default)</p>
        <p><del>&lt;del&gt;</del> - Deleted text (strikethrough by default)</p>
        <p><mark>&lt;mark&gt;</mark> - Highlighted/marked text</p>
      </div>
    </Container>

    <h3>Abbreviations</h3>
    <Container>
      <p>
        The <abbr title="World Wide Web Consortium">W3C</abbr> is the main international standards organization for the 
        <abbr title="World Wide Web">WWW</abbr>. Hover over abbreviations to see their full meaning.
      </p>
      <code class="text-sm text-secondary mt-2 block">&lt;abbr title="Full Text"&gt;SHORT&lt;/abbr&gt;</code>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- Specialized Elements -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2>Specialized Elements</h2>
    <p class="mb-8 text-secondary">Elements for quotes, code, and metadata.</p>

    <h3>Quotations</h3>
    <Container>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;blockquote&gt; - Block Quotation</h4>
          <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-4 py-2 my-4 italic">
            The only way to do great work is to love what you do. If you haven't found it yet, keep looking. Don't settle.
            <footer class="mt-2 text-sm text-secondary not-italic">â€” Steve Jobs</footer>
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;q&gt; - Inline Quotation</h4>
          <p>As Benjamin Franklin once said, <q>Tell me and I forget. Teach me and I remember. Involve me and I learn.</q></p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;cite&gt; - Citation</h4>
          <p>More information can be found in <cite>The Design of Everyday Things</cite> by Don Norman.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>

    <h3>Code &amp; Computer Text</h3>
    <Container>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;code&gt; - Inline Code</h4>
          <p>Use the <code class="bg-black/10 dark:bg-black/40 px-2 py-1 rounded">console.log()</code> function to debug your JavaScript.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;pre&gt; - Preformatted Text</h4>
          <pre class="p-4 bg-black/10 dark:bg-black/40 rounded overflow-x-auto">
<code>function greet(name) {'{'} 
  return `Hello, ${'${'}name{'}'}!`;
{'}'}

console.log(greet('World'));</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;kbd&gt; - Keyboard Input</h4>
          <p>Press <kbd class="bg-black/10 dark:bg-black/40 px-2 py-1 rounded border border-border">Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd class="bg-black/10 dark:bg-black/40 px-2 py-1 rounded border border-border">C</kbd> to copy.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;samp&gt; - Sample Output</h4>
          <p>The program returned: <samp class="bg-black/10 dark:bg-black/40 px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono">Error 404: File not found</samp></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>

    <h3>Metadata Elements</h3>
    <Container>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;address&gt; - Contact Information</h4>
          <address class="not-italic">
            <strong>Adrian's Viewpoint</strong><br>
            Email: <a href="mailto:contact@example.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">contact@example.com</a><br>
            Website: <a href="https://adrianviewpoint.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">adrianviewpoint.com</a>
          </address>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h4 class="mb-2">&lt;time&gt; - Date/Time</h4>
          <p>Article published on <time datetime="2025-11-26" class="font-semibold">November 26, 2025</time></p>
          <p>Meeting scheduled for <time datetime="2025-12-01T14:00" class="font-semibold">December 1, 2025 at 2:00 PM</time></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- Combined Example -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2>Real-World Example</h2>
    <p class="mb-8 text-secondary">A practical example combining multiple typography elements.</p>
    
    <Container as="article">
      <h3>Understanding Web Typography</h3>
      <p class="text-secondary"><time datetime="2025-11-26">November 26, 2025</time></p>
      
      <p class="mt-4">
        <strong>Typography</strong> is <em>fundamental</em> to good web design. As the <abbr title="World Wide Web Consortium">W3C</abbr> 
        states in their guidelines, proper use of semantic <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr> elements improves 
        both accessibility and <mark>search engine optimization</mark>.
      </p>
      
      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-4 py-2 my-4 italic">
        Good typography makes the act of reading effortless, while poor typography turns users away.
      </blockquote>
      
      <h4>Key Principles</h4>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>Use semantic HTML elements</li>
        <li>Maintain proper heading hierarchy</li>
        <li>Ensure sufficient contrast</li>
      </ol>
      
      <p>
        For example, use <code class="bg-black/10 dark:bg-black/40 px-2 py-1 rounded">&lt;strong&gt;</code> for 
        <strong>important text</strong> and <code class="bg-black/10 dark:bg-black/40 px-2 py-1 rounded">&lt;em&gt;</code> 
        for <em>emphasized text</em>.
      </p>
      
      <p class="mt-4">
        <small>Last updated: <time datetime="2025-11-26">November 26, 2025</time></small>
      </p>
    </Container>
  </section>
</StyleguideLayout>
